                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d751">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">McCormick</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">St. Petersburg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-01-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 7, 1905</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. McCormick states that in order to make the appeal in the case of the <hi
                        rend="italic">Arabia</hi> with any chance of success a sworn statement
                    should be sent to Mr. Berline that the Department of State was unable to
                    communicate directly with Vladisvostok, which created delay, and similar sworn
                    statements to that effect from the owners of the vessel sworn to before a
                    Russian consul.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
